Covid-19 infections have started rising, with the Health ministry yesterday announcing one death and 230 more infections, bringing the total to 98, 184.Kenya has 337,432 teachers serving in more than 30,000 public primary and post-primary schools. At least 36 tutors have died of Covid-19, the Teachers Service Commission (TSC) has said.
The latest data from the TSC shows that 345 teachers have reported being infected with the coronavirus.  Among them, 209 have since recovered while nine are in hospital. Another 92 are under the home-based care programme. The TSC said among the infected teachers, 159 are males while 186 are female.



